<br>
Mikel mentioned that the US should go into Iraq with all the &quot;nice toys&quot; that the US made during the cold war. From seeing this i am guessing he means Nuclear and Biological weapons.<br>
<br>
Now what gets us Europeans in this matter is that, for one the conflict is bloody close to our backyard. Lets say that curious George does decide to make Iraq a glass desert, purely hypotheticaly, there would be a very big chance that 1) if the airflow is going the wrong way, most of europe would be affected by this.<br>
2) that the arab countries would be so bloody angry that they will, And i have no doubt about this. invade Europe, or start a killing spree with suicide bombers etc. since we are also the &quot;evil west&quot; being the allies of the US.<br>
<br>
Granted something should be done about this, but... it is easy to sit relatively safe halfway across the world and condone things like this. Europeans are concerned about this because the major impact will be on us, not the United States.<br>
<br>
I still sit many a time and wonder what would the US have done if september 11th hadnt been a terrorist act against you. but lets say Paris or Berlin. Truely i believe that Bush would not have started a war against Al-qaeda. because after all it is europe and their problems.<br>
<br>
