<br>
The &quot;toys&quot; I meant are the tons of tanks, bombers, and weapons designed for a superpower ultra showdown of massive armies in the middle of Europe fighting the commie hordes. These toys are very powerful, but of only limited use against enemies like Al Qaeda, which hide out in the mountains and cities and avoid direct conflict. Against Saddam's Rebublican Guard tho, they can have a field day, like they did in the gulf war. <br>
<br>
Perhaps you are right in that the US would not have attacked Al Qaeda if were weren't directly attacked, but so what? You think France wouldn't have attacked if they were hit like this. Please. We WERE attacked, so we have every right to fight back. The fact that we have built a massively sophisticated and powerful army means most fights we are likely to win, but again, THEY PICKED THIS FIGHT. You throw a punch at the biggest guy in the bar, you can't complain when he starts kicking your ass.<br>
<br>
As for China, there are a few differences. Lets look at the reality here.<br>
<br>
1. China IS armed with nukes and biological weapons, so if we attack them to get rid of their nukes, they will nuke us. Therefore, the reality is, China is beyond our ability to disarm at the moment.<br>
<br>
2. China plays the game, they may be a brutal regime that opresses their people, but they play the game of diplomacy  and such that makes them slightly more acceptable. China has also had the nukes fro a long time and hasn't used them, so while I am sure the US does not like the fact China has nukes, it has pretty much come to accept it.<br>
<br>
3. China is NOT ruled by one man anymore. There is a government in system that will hopefully prevent one Chinese psycho from unleashing all their nukes. Saddam IS the government of Iraq, there is no system to stop him from nuking the hell of out anything once he gets nukes.<br>
<br>
And the Arabs are already killing your people. The Europeans would be better off getting on board this instead of trying to lecture the US about being warmongers. (Kinda ironic given Europe's history) They already hate you, they hate ALL of us, which is why Europe and the US need to work together on this, vs Al Qaeda if not Iraq.  <p><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/pbakas/mikel_sig2.jpg><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67382>See if your stuff is better then mine</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub141.ezboard.com/umikelmorbidus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mikel Morbidus</A> at: 10/14/02 1:55:26 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=519.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=519.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b> <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=519.topic&start=61&stop=65>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.showPrevMessage?topicID=519.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.showNextMessage?topicID=519.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=519.topic&index=60><img src=http://www.jennymarie.com/eqp/03reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.emailToFriend?topicID=519.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.threadControl?topicID=519.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/de